values.description:
This should upload the package to the s3 instance. Configuration must be done manually into the node for the upload, currently master is the only one doing this.

I've [found](http://zcox.wordpress.com/2012/08/13/hosting-a-private-apt-repository-on-s3/) [people](http://xn.pinkhamster.net/blog/tech/host-a-debian-repository-on-s3.html) running their own deb repository in s3 instances but seems like is always a sync from a local repository. I don't see too much benefit for it (a part from saving disk space).

@nkoenig, what do you think?

